modules.description: Provides operations to iterate over features, create zero vectors, and retrieve or update values associated with integer-based features. Works with a generic vector type parameterized by value type and indexed by integers. Used to manage sparse feature representations in machine learning models.

provides a framework for defining and processing request for comments by combining specialized components. it includes data types for representing requests, responses, and metadata, along with operations for validation, parsing, and transformation. users can create structured RFC documents, enforce formatting rules, and generate standardized outputs. examples include generating a template for a new RFC, checking compliance with existing standards, and extracting key fields from a submitted draft.

Provides functions to train and predict with random forests, compute R² scores, and manage model persistence. Operates on samples consisting of features and dependent variables, and forests composed of trees and indices. Used to generate predictions from training data, evaluate model performance using OOB samples, and save or load trained models to disk.

Generates and evaluates random forest models using bootstrapped data and out-of-bag error estimation. Processes labeled tabular data with categorical and numerical features, supporting both classification and regression tasks. Enables quick model training and performance assessment without requiring a separate test set.

combines vector manipulation, RFC processing, and random forest modeling into a unified toolkit. it handles sparse feature vectors, structured RFC documents, and machine learning models with associated metrics and persistence. users can manage feature data, generate and validate RFCs, and train or deploy predictive models. examples include creating feature vectors for sparse data, generating RFC templates, and evaluating model accuracy with R² scores.
